  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Vulnerable Refugees and Local Communities in Cox&apos;s Bazar, Bangladesh, Through Improved Health, Protection, and Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this multi-sectoral project in Cox&apos;s Bazar (Bangladesh), IOM aims to reduce protection threats and vulnerabilities while increasing local capacities, reduce excess mortality from common morbidities and support vulnerable refugees and local communities through improved water, sanitation and hygiene services (WASH). Protection activities will provide life-saving services to prevent and respond to gender-based violence, child abuse, human trafficking and other protection risks, incidents and threats as well as to support persons with disabilities to have access to services. Further, health activities will provide lifesaving assistance to refugees by strengthening the health systems in the refugee camps and local communities. Finally, comprehensive WASH services will be maintained and monitored to prevent disease outbreaks.</narrative>
  </description>
